title: A novel addressable 9600-microwell array single cell RNA-seq method applied on fresh mouse cortical cells and frozen human cortical nuclei
abstract: We adopted the STRT-seq [Islam et al., Nat Methods 11, 163-166 (2013)] RNA-seq technology to a 9600-well array and applied it to analyze single cells from mouse and human cortex single cells.
overall_design: 2192 single cells from mouse somatosensory cortex and 2028 single nuclei from human post-mortem middle temporal gyrus cortex.
summary: We adopted the STRT-seq [Islam et al., Nat Methods 11, 163-166 (2013)] RNA-seq technology to a 9600-well array and applied it to analyze single cells from mouse and human cortex single cells.
